SIMPLE: pillow
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pillow
<hw>Pil"low</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>pilwe</ets>,
AS. <ets>pyle</ets>, fr. L. <ets>pilvinus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Anything used to support the head of a person when reposing;
especially, a sack or case filled with feathers, down, hair, or other
soft material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Resty sloth] finds the down <qex>pillow</qex> hard.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A piece of metal or wood, forming
a support to equalize pressure; a brass; a pillow block.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A block under the inner end of a
bowsprit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A kind of plain, coarse fustian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lace pillow</b></col>, <cd>a cushion used in making
hand-wrought lace.</cd> -- <col><b>Pillow bier</b></col> <ety>[OE.
<ets>pilwebere</ets>; cf. LG. <ets>b⟦uum⟧re</ets> a pillowcase]</ety>,
<cd>a pillowcase; pillow slip.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<au>Chaucer.</au> -- <col><b>Pillow block</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>,
<cd>a block, or standard, for supporting a journal, as of a shaft. It is
usually bolted to the frame or foundation of a machine, and is often
furnished with journal boxes, and a movable cover, or cap, for
tightening the bearings by means of bolts; -- called also
<altname>pillar block</altname>, or <altname>plumber
block</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Pillow lace</b></col>, <cd>handmade
lace wrought with bobbins upon a lace pillow.</cd> -- <col><b>Pillow of
a plow</b></col>, <cd>a crosspiece of wood which serves to raise or
lower the beam.</cd> -- <col><b>Pillow sham</b></col>, <cd>an ornamental
covering laid over a pillow when not in use.</cd> -- <col><b>Pillow
slip</b></col>, <cd>a pillowcase.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pillow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pillow
<hw>Pil"low</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Pillowed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pillowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To rest or lay upon,
or as upon, a pillow; to support; <as>as, to <ex>pillow</ex> the
head</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pillows</qex> his chin upon an orient wave.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pillowcase</ent>⟦br⟧
